This U.S. State Privacy Notice (“
State Notice
”) provides more information on the personal data (also referred to herein as “personal information”) we collect and your rights under United States privacy laws.
We collect personal data for business purposes described in our
General Privacy Notice
and our
Offerings Privacy Notice
under the sections “How We Use Personal Data.”
We will only share or disclose your data as described in our
General Privacy Notice
and our
Offerings Privacy Notice
under the sections “How We Share Personal Data.”
Subject to certain limitations and local data protection laws, you have the right to:
Access your personal data;
Erase or delete your personal data;
Restrict our processing of your personal data;
Rectify or correct your personal data;
Port your personal data to another Controller;
Object to certain processing of your personal data;
Opt out of certain disclosures of your personal data to third parties;
Withdraw your consent to use your personal data;
Object to any decision based solely on automated processing, including profiling; and
Not be discriminated against for exercising your rights as described above.
We will authenticate your identity via email verification when you exercise your rights.
To exercise any of these rights, please complete this
form
. For more information on how to exercise these personal rights, see our
Privacy Notice
.
Data Collection History
For details about the personal data we have collected and data we may collect in the future, including sources of collection, please see “Personal Data We Collect” in our
General Privacy Notice
, with additional detail outlined in our
General Privacy Notice Table
. If you are a user of our Offerings, this information is also available in “Personal Data We Collect” in our
Offerings Privacy Notice
, and in the
Offerings Privacy Notice Table
. Our
Cookie Notice
explains how we have, and may continue to use, cookies, pixels, and similar tracking technologies to gather information about your use of, and automated interactions with, the Sites and Offerings, and your rights to control our use of them.
Other Rights
The following are other rights afforded to you according to respective state laws:
California
You have the right to request more details about the categories or specific pieces of personal information we have collected about you over the last 12 months (including how we use and disclose this information);
We do not sell our customers’ personal information as defined in the California Consumer Privacy Act, and we will not sell such personal information without providing any required notice and/or right to opt-out of such sale. However, if you are a California resident, you may opt out of any future sales by contacting us as described in the section "
How to Contact Us
." We may request additional information to verify your identity.
California, Colorado, Connecticut, Delaware, Montana, Nebraska, New Hampshire, New Jersey, Oregon, and Texas
You have the option to set or change your web browser controls to accept or refuse cookies by clicking the "Your Privacy Choices" link at the bottom of our Site. For more information, see the “Your Choices” section of our
Cookie Notice
.
Nevada
We do not sell your data as defined by Nevada's Senate Bill 220.
Oregon
We do not use de-identified data and would not re-identify any de-identified data we happen to obtain.
Washington
We do not collect consumer health data as defined under Washington’s My Health My Data Act. If we do collect any consumer health data, it will be with your consent and for a specified purpose.
Last Updated: July 19, 2024
